Package ca.c301.t03_model

Class Summary
Base64 Encodes and decodes to and from Base64 notation.
Base64.InputStream A Base64.InputStream will read data from another java.io.InputStream, given in the constructor, and encode/decode to/from Base64 notation on the fly.
Base64.OutputStream A Base64.OutputStream will write data to another java.io.OutputStream, given in the constructor, and encode/decode to/from Base64 notation on the fly.
Camera Handles camera and photo operations
DataManager Handles all input/output required for the application
DisplayConverter Class containing functions required to convert data for display in list views
ElasticSearchResponse<T> Handles elastic search results
ElasticSearchSearchResponse<T> Handles elastic search results
EmailHandler Handles email operations.
Hits<T> Handles elastic search hits
HTTPManager Contains functions that handle all web related functionality, most of the adding and searching of recipes is heavily based off of the ESDemo code.
Ingredient Ingredient object used in both recipes and virtual pantry to store name, amount, and unit of measurement
IngredientDatabaseHandler Handles the Ingredients Database, which is also called Virtual Pantry
Recipe Recipe object used to store name, instructions, and ingredients
RecipeDatabaseHandler Handles the Recipes Database, which are the local recipes
RecipeManager Handles recipe manipulation
RecipePhoto Handles storage of photos for recipes
SerializeHandler Handles Serialization and Deserialization of Objects
